    <abstract id="aspace_56f7e17d3450eb8c7ff22ca1e7bdf941">Copies of two muster rolls of a company of detached militia under the command of Capt. Thomas Floyd Jones in the 2nd Regiment of the New York State Infantry commanded by Lieut. Col. Daniel Bedell. The company was organized near Fort Greene, Brooklyn, New York. The muster rolls include soldier lists from September 1814 to November 1814.</abstract>
